                  <p> Thanks to Emmanuel Francis for providing us with the reference to this
                     colophon and a draft translation of its content. (2) Concerning the name of the
                     owner, note that Fabricius dictionary  lists <foreign xml:lang="tam-Latn" > karuṇikkaṉ</foreign> as a
                     synonym of <foreign xml:lang="tam-Latn" >karṇaṉ</foreign> (“village accountant”) and that <foreign xml:lang="tam-Latn" >oḻukaraiyuṭaiyār</foreign> probably
                     refers to the name of the Lord at Oḻukarai, possibly a suburb of Pondicherry
                  </p>
